LXVI. 38. trinis castris: marked VVV on Plan XIII. From the place where he was joined by Labienus (Joigny on the Yonne, south· east of Agedincum), Caesar had marched eastward, and was now east of Dijon‚ near the little river Vingeanne, a tributary of the Saone. Here the engagement described in Chapters 56, 57, took place.
